Class CodemlAncestralSiteOutputParser.Branch

  • java.lang.Object
    • uk.ac.qmul.sbcs.evolution.convergence.handlers.documents.parsers.codeml.CodemlAncestralSiteOutputParser.Branch
  • Enclosing class:
    CodemlAncestralSiteOutputParser

    public class CodemlAncestralSiteOutputParser.Branch
extends java.lang.Object
    Internal class to represent branch (pairs of nodes) which are compared in a branch-pair comparison.

    Note that the contains() method is not an implementation of java.util.Set#contains(), or subclass of e.g. java.util.HashSet#contains().

    Author:
    Joe Parker, Kitson Consulting / Queen Mary University of London
    See Also:
    BranchPairComparison}

        public int otherNode(int some_node)

        Given a node UID, checks whether this branch contains this node. If so returns the other node UID. If not, throws NullPointerException
        Parameters:
